# <%= current_page.data.title %>

## Status

✅ Accepted

## Context

The modernisation platform have a lambda module which uses lambda containers with an ECR image. Alternatively, code can be zipped with a lambda directly.

## Decision

We are going to use containerised lambdas.

## Consequences

### General consequences

* All lambda images will be pushed to an ECR repo

### Advantages

* Ease of lambda versioning
* Larger memory to add custom libraries than normal lambda (10GB vs 250mb in base lambda)

### Disadvantages

* Lambda code is not visible on the AWS console.
* Lambda images have to be pushed from a separate repo to the other infrastructure code, so deployment is more complicated.